I suspect this is a test issue ... I'm not sure if we really meant for this high number of operations (notice that the map version of this test sets this to 1000 vs. 10000):
```
   final int numQueues = 30;
   final int numOperations = 10000;
```

In addition, we're creating a new HAEventWrapper for each message * each queue ...
In reality the CacheClientNotifier (deliverMessage) hands the same HAEventWrapper to each proxy ... so we don't need 30 HAEventWrappers for each of these 10000 operations.

We could move that up out of the loop to have this:
```
    for (int i = 0; i < numOperations; i++) {
      count.set(i);

      // CacheClientNotifier creates a single HAEventWrapper containing the ClientUpdateMessage
      // and this is enqueued for each client (CacheClientNotifier.singletonRouteClientMessage)
      ClientUpdateMessage message = new ClientUpdateMessageImpl(EnumListenerEvent.AFTER_CREATE,
          (LocalRegion) dataRegion, "key", "value".getBytes(), (byte) 0x01, null,
          new ClientProxyMembershipID(), new EventID(new byte[] {1}, 1, count.get()));

      queues.parallelStream().forEach(haRegionQueue -> {
        try {
          HAEventWrapper haEventWrapper = new HAEventWrapper(message);

          testValidationWrapperSet.add(haEventWrapper);

          haRegionQueue.put(haEventWrapper);
        } catch (InterruptedException iex) {
          throw new RuntimeException(iex);
        }
      });
    }
```

@jdeppe-pivotal @upthewaterspout 

I have changed the property to be `ssl-use-default-sslcontext` which is more appropriate to the intended behavior.  This gives users to choose between whether to use a default SSLContext or let Geode configure with specific settings (stores, managers, protocols and ciphers). When `ssl-user-default-sslcontext` is set a default SSLContext is used using `SSLContext.getDefault()`.

So in SocketCreator, we can chose between creating default context vs configuring with user provided settings as in:
```
geode-core/src/main/java/org/apache/geode/internal/net/SocketCreator.java

private SSLContext createAndConfigureSSLContext() throws GeneralSecurityException, IOException {

    if (sslConfig.useDefaultSSLContext()) {
      return SSLContext.getDefault();
    }

    SSLContext newSSLContext = getSSLContextInstance();
    KeyManager[] keyManagers = getKeyManagers();
    TrustManager[] trustManagers = getTrustManagers();

    newSSLContext.init(keyManagers, trustManagers, null /* use the default secure random */);
    return newSSLContext;
  }
```

